sentences: Ann Sheppard Mounsey, or Ann Mounsey Bartholomew on marriage (17 April 1811 – 24 June 1891), was born at 21 Old Compton Street, Soho, London, the eldest child of Thomas Mounsey, a licensed victualler, and his wife, Mary, née Briggs.
After 1828 she became the organist at various London churches, serving at St Vedast Foster Lane for nearly fifty years.
